<br>
Unless WMD are located, then Bush Jr. is forced to admit he LIED to the American public -- and the world.  That lie is of such massive magnitude to be an impeachable offense.  It's a good thing the Republicans control both the House of Representatives and the Senate.<br>
<br>
Modified milk trucks are not weapons of mass destruction.  Exactly zero traces of chemical or biological agents have been detected on those trucks.  Without the presence of those agents, those trucks can in no manner be considered as weapons of mass destruction.  They are just trucks.<br>
<br>
Let's suppose some country is accused of creating a nuclear bomb, and the preferred delivery method is to drop it from a bomber.  The presense of a bomber in that country's air force does is not proof that they have a nuclear bomb.<br>
<br>
As for Al Qaeda, there have been exactly ZERO people associated with Al Qaeda or Saddam's administration who have corraborated the link.  The only evidence presented as proof of a link is &quot;they both hate the US&quot; and &quot;they are both from the middle east&quot;.  Those statements are true of just about every middle-eastern country.<br>
<br>
The United States has been waging a continual, illegal air war against Iraq for more than a decade.  If Iraq were to strike back against the US territory, then it would be just a continuation of the war that already existed.  It would not be an act of terrorism for Iraq to retaliate against an aggressor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1068<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/10/03 9:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Must suck to be wrong....LIED TO</span><hr size=1> There is nothing illegal about the war.  It is entirely supported by UN resolutions.<br>
<br>
I don't believe that Bush lied in any way.  There exists the possibility that he was mistaken (although the trucks are sufficient evidence for me to entirely discount that possibility).  However, even if he were wrong, it doesn't matter as far as legality.  I don't base justification for the legality of the war on WMD's.  WMD's are only part of the equation in deciding whether we should have invaded.  The fact that he kicked the inspectors out and failed to live up to UN resolutions or the fact that he invaded Kuwait is enough for me to conclude that the war was legal.  If, by some bizarre chance, it turned out we were wrong on every single item I list as a reason why the war was a good idea (he had no WMD's, he had no terrorist links, the Iraqi people all loved him more than their mother, etc), then that would simply mean that the war was a bad decision on our part, albeit one which we were entirely justified in making.  i.e. The decision was ours to make either way, we had the authority to do it, but it was a waste of resources.<br>
<br>
To give an analogy, say you own your own company.  You have 2 great employees and 2 horrible employees.  You have the right to fire any of them.  If you fire the 2 good employees, and keep the 2 horrible employees, you are within your rights.  Your company goes out of business because it was a bad choice, but it was your choice to make.  His refusal to live up to the terms of surrender made the war legal and within our rights, all the rest simply involved us deciding whether it was worth it or not.<br>
<br>
